{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":996,"text":"So recently, we heard a lot about\nhow social media helps empower protest,"},{"time":5802,"text":"and that's true,"},{"time":7181,"text":"but after more than a decade"},{"time":8836,"text":"of studying and participating\nin multiple social movements,"},{"time":12501,"text":"I've come to realize"},{"time":14303,"text":"that the way technology\nempowers social movements"},{"time":17614,"text":"can also paradoxically help weaken them."},{"time":20720,"text":"This is not inevitable,\nbut overcoming it requires diving deep"},{"time":24604,"text":"into what makes success possible\nover the long term."},{"time":28897,"text":"And the lessons apply in multiple domains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31458,"text":"Now, take Turkey's\nGezi Park protests, July 2013,"},{"time":35453,"text":"which I went back to study in the field."},{"time":38490,"text":"Twitter was key to its organizing."},{"time":40943,"text":"It was everywhere in the park --\nwell, along with a lot of tear gas."},{"time":44337,"text":"It wasn't all high tech."},{"time":46175,"text":"But the people in Turkey had already\ngotten used to the power of Twitter"},{"time":50053,"text":"because of an unfortunate incident\nabout a year before"},{"time":53994,"text":"when military jets had bombed and killed"},{"time":57785,"text":"34 Kurdish smugglers\nnear the border region,"},{"time":61874,"text":"and Turkish media completely\ncensored this news."},{"time":66618,"text":"Editors sat in their newsrooms"},{"time":68456,"text":"and waited for the government\nto tell them what to do."},{"time":71355,"text":"One frustrated journalist\ncould not take this anymore."},{"time":73955,"text":"He purchased his own plane ticket,"},{"time":75645,"text":"and went to the village\nwhere this had occurred."},{"time":77957,"text":"And he was confronted by this scene:"},{"time":80623,"text":"a line of coffins coming down a hill,\nrelatives wailing."},{"time":86021,"text":"He later he told me\nhow overwhelmed he felt,"},{"time":88462,"text":"and didn't know what to do,"},{"time":90183,"text":"so he took out his phone,"},{"time":92156,"text":"like any one of us might,"},{"time":93924,"text":"and snapped that picture\nand tweeted it out."},{"time":97122,"text":"And voila, that picture went viral"},{"time":100849,"text":"and broke the censorship\nand forced mass media to cover it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105237,"text":"So when, a year later,\nTurkey's Gezi protests happened,"},{"time":108418,"text":"it started as a protest\nabout a park being razed,"},{"time":111140,"text":"but became an anti-authoritarian protest."},{"time":113443,"text":"It wasn't surprising\nthat media also censored it,"},{"time":117601,"text":"but it got a little ridiculous at times."},{"time":120533,"text":"When things were so intense,"},{"time":122603,"text":"when CNN International\nwas broadcasting live from Istanbul,"},{"time":126998,"text":"CNN Turkey instead was broadcasting\na documentary on penguins."},{"time":133351,"text":"Now, I love penguin documentaries,\nbut that wasn't the news of the day."},{"time":137934,"text":"An angry viewer put his two screens\ntogether and snapped that picture,"},{"time":142231,"text":"and that one too went viral,"},{"time":144098,"text":"and since then, people call Turkish media\nthe penguin media. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":148586,"text":"But this time, people knew what to do."},{"time":150751,"text":"They just took out their phones\nand looked for actual news."},{"time":153710,"text":"Better, they knew to go to the park\nand take pictures and participate"},{"time":158174,"text":"and share it more on social media."},{"time":160125,"text":"Digital connectivity was used\nfor everything from food to donations."},{"time":166675,"text":"Everything was organized partially\nwith the help of these new technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171947,"text":"And using Internet to mobilize\nand publicize protests"},{"time":176153,"text":"actually goes back a long way."},{"time":178609,"text":"Remember the Zapatistas,"},{"time":180454,"text":"the peasant uprising\nin the southern Chiapas region of Mexico"},{"time":185089,"text":"led by the masked, pipe-smoking,\ncharismatic Subcomandante Marcos?"},{"time":190720,"text":"That was probably the first movement"},{"time":192599,"text":"that got global attention\nthanks to the Internet."},{"time":195690,"text":"Or consider Seattle '99,"},{"time":197338,"text":"when a multinational grassroots effort\nbrought global attention"},{"time":202141,"text":"to what was then an obscure organization,\nthe World Trade Organization,"},{"time":206826,"text":"by also utilizing these digital\ntechnologies to help them organize."},{"time":211367,"text":"And more recently, movement after movement"},{"time":213902,"text":"has shaken country after country:"},{"time":216740,"text":"the Arab uprisings from Bahrain\nto Tunisia to Egypt and more;"},{"time":221872,"text":"indignados in Spain, Italy, Greece;\nthe Gezi Park protests;"},{"time":226744,"text":"Taiwan; Euromaidan in Ukraine; Hong Kong."},{"time":230968,"text":"And think of more recent initiatives,\nlike the #BringBackOurGirls hashtags."},{"time":235680,"text":"Nowadays, a network of tweets\ncan unleash a global awareness campaign."},{"time":242536,"text":"A Facebook page can become the hub\nof a massive mobilization."},{"time":246454,"text":"Amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248224,"text":"But think of the moments I just mentioned."},{"time":252538,"text":"The achievements they were\nable to have, their outcomes,"},{"time":257203,"text":"are not really proportional\nto the size and energy they inspired."},{"time":262013,"text":"The hopes they rightfully raised\nare not really matched"},{"time":266034,"text":"by what they were able to have\nas a result in the end."},{"time":270502,"text":"And this raises a question:"},{"time":274204,"text":"As digital technology makes things\neasier for movements,"},{"time":278429,"text":"why haven't successful outcomes\nbecome more likely as well?"},{"time":282452,"text":"In embracing digital platforms\nfor activism and politics,"},{"time":288017,"text":"are we overlooking some of the benefits\nof doing things the hard way?"},{"time":292251,"text":"Now, I believe so."},{"time":293468,"text":"I believe that the rule of thumb is:"},{"time":295273,"text":"Easier to mobilize does not always mean\neasier to achieve gains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300610,"text":"Now, to be clear,"},{"time":303503,"text":"technology does empower in multiple ways."},{"time":306357,"text":"It's very powerful."},{"time":307817,"text":"In Turkey, I watched\nfour young college students"},{"time":311863,"text":"organize a countrywide citizen journalism\nnetwork called 140Journos"},{"time":316093,"text":"that became the central hub\nfor uncensored news in the country."},{"time":320524,"text":"In Egypt, I saw another four young people\nuse digital connectivity"},{"time":325671,"text":"to organize the supplies and logistics\nfor 10 field hospitals,"},{"time":329518,"text":"very large operations,"},{"time":331529,"text":"during massive clashes\nnear Tahrir Square in 2011."},{"time":337500,"text":"And I asked the founder\nof this effort, called Tahrir Supplies,"},{"time":341217,"text":"how long it took him to go from when\nhe had the idea to when he got started."},{"time":347327,"text":"\"Five minutes,\" he said. Five minutes."},{"time":349686,"text":"And he had no training\nor background in logistics."},{"time":352234,"text":"Or think of the Occupy movement\nwhich rocked the world in 2011."},{"time":355957,"text":"It started with a single email"},{"time":357935,"text":"from a magazine, Adbusters,\nto 90,000 subscribers in its list."},{"time":363176,"text":"About two months after that first email,"},{"time":366160,"text":"there were in the United States\n600 ongoing occupations and protests."},{"time":372509,"text":"Less than one month after the first\nphysical occupation in Zuccotti Park,"},{"time":378333,"text":"a global protest was held\nin about 82 countries, 950 cities."},{"time":385174,"text":"It was one of the largest\nglobal protests ever organized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":387919,"text":"Now, compare that to what the Civil Rights\nMovement had to do in 1955 Alabama"},{"time":394606,"text":"to protest the racially segregated\nbus system, which they wanted to boycott."},{"time":400743,"text":"They'd been preparing for many years"},{"time":402495,"text":"and decided it was time\nto swing into action"},{"time":404561,"text":"after Rosa Parks was arrested."},{"time":406764,"text":"But how do you get the word out --"},{"time":408430,"text":"tomorrow we're going to\nstart the boycott --"},{"time":410593,"text":"when you don't have Facebook,\ntexting, Twitter, none of that?"},{"time":416001,"text":"So they had to mimeograph 52,000 leaflets"},{"time":421171,"text":"by sneaking into a university\nduplicating room"},{"time":424364,"text":"and working all night, secretly."},{"time":426905,"text":"They then used the 68\nAfrican-American organizations"},{"time":430398,"text":"that criss-crossed the city\nto distribute those leaflets by hand."},{"time":434365,"text":"And the logistical tasks were daunting,\nbecause these were poor people."},{"time":439335,"text":"They had to get to work, boycott or no,"},{"time":441425,"text":"so a massive carpool was organized,"},{"time":444327,"text":"again by meeting."},{"time":446443,"text":"No texting, no Twitter, no Facebook."},{"time":448838,"text":"They had to meet almost all the time\nto keep this carpool going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452407,"text":"Today, it would be so much easier."},{"time":454679,"text":"We could create a database,\navailable rides and what rides you need,"},{"time":459667,"text":"have the database coordinate,\nand use texting."},{"time":462949,"text":"We wouldn't have to meet all that much."},{"time":465503,"text":"But again, consider this:"},{"time":467779,"text":"the Civil Rights Movement\nin the United States"},{"time":470773,"text":"navigated a minefield\nof political dangers,"},{"time":475267,"text":"faced repression and overcame,\nwon major policy concessions,"},{"time":480770,"text":"navigated and innovated through risks."},{"time":484006,"text":"In contrast, three years\nafter Occupy sparked"},{"time":487539,"text":"that global conversation about inequality,"},{"time":490145,"text":"the policies that fueled it\nare still in place."},{"time":493970,"text":"Europe was also rocked\nby anti-austerity protests,"},{"time":497115,"text":"but the continent\ndidn't shift its direction."},{"time":501237,"text":"In embracing these technologies,"},{"time":504173,"text":"are we overlooking some of the benefits\nof slow and sustained?"},{"time":510581,"text":"To understand this,"},{"time":512450,"text":"I went back to Turkey\nabout a year after the Gezi protests"},{"time":515573,"text":"and I interviewed a range of people,"},{"time":517850,"text":"from activists to politicians,"},{"time":521557,"text":"from both the ruling party\nand the opposition party and movements."},{"time":526174,"text":"I found that the Gezi protesters\nwere despairing."},{"time":529480,"text":"They were frustrated,"},{"time":531511,"text":"and they had achieved much less\nthan what they had hoped for."},{"time":534567,"text":"This echoed what I'd been hearing\naround the world"},{"time":537105,"text":"from many other protesters\nthat I'm in touch with."},{"time":540891,"text":"And I've come to realize\nthat part of the problem"},{"time":543198,"text":"is that today's protests have become\na bit like climbing Mt. Everest"},{"time":549067,"text":"with the help of 60 Sherpas,"},{"time":551524,"text":"and the Internet is our Sherpa."},{"time":554651,"text":"What we're doing is taking the fast routes"},{"time":558964,"text":"and not replacing the benefits\nof the slower work."},{"time":562303,"text":"Because, you see,"},{"time":563999,"text":"the kind of work that went into organizing"},{"time":566867,"text":"all those daunting,\ntedious logistical tasks"},{"time":569650,"text":"did not just take care of those tasks,"},{"time":572279,"text":"they also created the kind of organization\nthat could think together collectively"},{"time":576963,"text":"and make hard decisions together,"},{"time":579238,"text":"create consensus and innovate,\nand maybe even more crucially,"},{"time":583175,"text":"keep going together through differences."},{"time":586542,"text":"So when you see this\nMarch on Washington in 1963,"},{"time":591330,"text":"when you look at that picture,"},{"time":593014,"text":"where this is the march where\nMartin Luther King gave his famous"},{"time":596355,"text":"\"I have a dream\" speech, 1963,"},{"time":599207,"text":"you don't just see a march\nand you don't just hear a powerful speech,"},{"time":603649,"text":"you also see the painstaking,\nlong-term work that can put on that march."},{"time":609122,"text":"And if you're in power,"},{"time":610917,"text":"you realize you have to take\nthe capacity signaled by that march,"},{"time":615218,"text":"not just the march, but the capacity\nsignaled by that march, seriously."},{"time":619724,"text":"In contrast, when you look\nat Occupy's global marches"},{"time":623727,"text":"that were organized in two weeks,"},{"time":625369,"text":"you see a lot of discontent,"},{"time":626753,"text":"but you don't necessarily see teeth that\ncan bite over the long term."},{"time":631617,"text":"And crucially, the Civil Rights Movement\ninnovated tactically"},{"time":635710,"text":"from boycotts to lunch counter sit-ins\nto pickets to marches to freedom rides."},{"time":642496,"text":"Today's movements scale up very quickly\nwithout the organizational base"},{"time":646311,"text":"that can see them through the challenges."},{"time":648900,"text":"They feel a little like startups\nthat got very big"},{"time":652700,"text":"without knowing what to do next,"},{"time":654705,"text":"and they rarely manage to shift tactically"},{"time":657362,"text":"because they don't have\nthe depth of capacity"},{"time":659859,"text":"to weather such transitions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662151,"text":"Now, I want to be clear:\nThe magic is not in the mimeograph."},{"time":667668,"text":"It's in that capacity to work together,\nthink together collectively,"},{"time":673489,"text":"which can only be built\nover time with a lot of work."},{"time":676671,"text":"To understand all this,"},{"time":678747,"text":"I interviewed a top official\nfrom the ruling party in Turkey,"},{"time":682571,"text":"and I ask him, \"How do you do it?\""},{"time":684739,"text":"They too use digital technology\nextensively, so that's not it."},{"time":688442,"text":"So what's the secret?"},{"time":690372,"text":"Well, he told me."},{"time":691896,"text":"He said the key is\nhe never took sugar with his tea."},{"time":698532,"text":"I said, what has that\ngot to do with anything?"},{"time":701593,"text":"Well, he said, his party starts\ngetting ready for the next election"},{"time":704759,"text":"the day after the last one,"},{"time":706300,"text":"and he spends all day every day\nmeeting with voters in their homes,"},{"time":710281,"text":"in their wedding parties,\ncircumcision ceremonies,"},{"time":712863,"text":"and then he meets with his colleagues\nto compare notes."},{"time":715818,"text":"With that many meetings every day,\nwith tea offered at every one of them,"},{"time":720384,"text":"which he could not refuse,\nbecause that would be rude,"},{"time":723736,"text":"he could not take even one cube of sugar\nper cup of tea,"},{"time":728379,"text":"because that would be many kilos of sugar,\nhe can't even calculate how many kilos,"},{"time":732335,"text":"and at that point I realized\nwhy he was speaking so fast."},{"time":735979,"text":"We had met in the afternoon,\nand he was already way over-caffeinated."},{"time":740527,"text":"But his party won two major elections"},{"time":745000,"text":"within a year of the Gezi protests\nwith comfortable margins."},{"time":748658,"text":"To be sure, governments have\ndifferent resources to bring to the table."},{"time":751997,"text":"It's not the same game,\nbut the differences are instructive."},{"time":755154,"text":"And like all such stories, this is not\na story just of technology."},{"time":759009,"text":"It's what technology allows us to do\nconverging with what we want to do."},{"time":764091,"text":"Today's social movements\nwant to operate informally."},{"time":767877,"text":"They do not want institutional leadership."},{"time":770147,"text":"They want to stay out of politics because\nthey fear corruption and cooptation."},{"time":775013,"text":"They have a point."},{"time":776546,"text":"Modern representative democracies\nare being strangled in many countries"},{"time":779961,"text":"by powerful interests."},{"time":782244,"text":"But operating this way\nmakes it hard for them"},{"time":785518,"text":"to sustain over the long term\nand exert leverage over the system,"},{"time":789268,"text":"which leads to frustrated\nprotesters dropping out,"},{"time":792530,"text":"and even more corrupt politics."},{"time":795889,"text":"And politics and democracy\nwithout an effective challenge hobbles,"},{"time":800977,"text":"because the causes that have inspired\nthe modern recent movements are crucial."},{"time":807370,"text":"Climate change is barreling towards us."},{"time":810465,"text":"Inequality is stifling human growth\nand potential and economies."},{"time":815348,"text":"Authoritarianism is choking\nmany countries."},{"time":817633,"text":"We need movements to be more effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820384,"text":"Now, some people have argued\nthat the problem is"},{"time":823062,"text":"today's movements are not formed of people\nwho take as many risks as before,"},{"time":829521,"text":"and that is not true."},{"time":831569,"text":"From Gezi to Tahrir to elsewhere,"},{"time":834131,"text":"I've seen people put their lives\nand livelihoods on the line."},{"time":837769,"text":"It's also not true,\nas Malcolm Gladwell claimed,"},{"time":840188,"text":"that today's protesters\nform weaker virtual ties."},{"time":842930,"text":"No, they come to these protests,\njust like before,"},{"time":846721,"text":"with their friends, existing networks,"},{"time":849333,"text":"and sometimes they do\nmake new friends for life."},{"time":851635,"text":"I still see the friends that I made"},{"time":854221,"text":"in those Zapatista-convened\nglobal protests more than a decade ago,"},{"time":857643,"text":"and the bonds between strangers\nare not worthless."},{"time":860615,"text":"When I got tear-gassed in Gezi,"},{"time":862899,"text":"people I didn't know helped me\nand one another instead of running away."},{"time":868171,"text":"In Tahrir, I saw people, protesters,"},{"time":871398,"text":"working really hard to keep\neach other safe and protected."},{"time":874208,"text":"And digital awareness-raising is great,"},{"time":876097,"text":"because changing minds\nis the bedrock of changing politics."},{"time":879816,"text":"But movements today have to move beyond\nparticipation at great scale very fast"},{"time":887216,"text":"and figure out how\nto think together collectively,"},{"time":890715,"text":"develop strong policy proposals,\ncreate consensus,"},{"time":894456,"text":"figure out the political steps\nand relate them to leverage,"},{"time":898130,"text":"because all these good intentions\nand bravery and sacrifice by itself"},{"time":901813,"text":"are not going to be enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903485,"text":"And there are many efforts."},{"time":905381,"text":"In New Zealand, a group of young people\nare developing a platform called Loomio"},{"time":909770,"text":"for participatory\ndecision making at scale."},{"time":912771,"text":"In Turkey, 140Journos\nare holding hack-a-thons"},{"time":916046,"text":"so that they support communities\nas well as citizen journalism."},{"time":920619,"text":"In Argentina, an open-source platform\ncalled DemocracyOS"},{"time":923725,"text":"is bringing participation\nto parliaments and political parties."},{"time":927133,"text":"These are all great, and we need more,"},{"time":930518,"text":"but the answer won't just be\nbetter online decision-making,"},{"time":934694,"text":"because to update democracy, we are going\nto need to innovate at every level,"},{"time":940247,"text":"from the organizational\nto the political to the social."},{"time":944740,"text":"Because to succeed over the long term,"},{"time":948692,"text":"sometimes you do need tea without sugar"},{"time":951064,"text":"along with your Twitter."},{"time":952697,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":954209,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}